ise as it won its first medal since 2008, walking away with bronze in the all-around team final.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999589601419585, \"rank\": 0.0003922178136485725, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. team beat expectations as it was carried by incredible performances from each member of the relatively young team, including suburban Chicago-nativePaul Juda.\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. team - made up of Frederick Richard, Brody Malone, Paul Juda, Asher Hong and Stephen Nedoroscik - finished with a score of 257.793, narrowly falling below China and Japan, widely considered top medal favorites for the event, but who both suffered major falls.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1767, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3335727363002667e-14, \"text\": \"Frederick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"score\": 0.9999538601865893, \"rank\": 4.229420481754906e-05, \"text\": \"Brody\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\"}, {\"begin\": 1800, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Juda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Juda\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Juda\", \"dbpedia\": \"